<ns3397:section xmlns:ns3397="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xml:id="resources.information.technologies.java.j2se.security.protectingSourceCode.usingByteCodeEncryptionDecryption">
    
    <ns3398:title xmlns:ns3398="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Using Byte-Code Encryption/Decryption</ns3398:title>

<ns3399:para xmlns:ns3399="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">One may also choose to encrypt the byte code and use a decryption plug-in when
the client loads the byte code into the run-time environment. This may work with 
clients you are willing to trust but in practice it usually requires that you
use hardware.</ns3399:para> 
<ns3400:para xmlns:ns3400="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
The disadvantages of using hardware decryption technologies are
<ns3401:itemizedlist xmlns:ns3401="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
  <ns3402:listitem xmlns:ns3402="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns3403:para xmlns:ns3403="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Increased cost.</ns3403:para></ns3402:listitem>
  <ns3404:listitem xmlns:ns3404="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns3405:para xmlns:ns3405="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">More difficult to distribute code.</ns3405:para></ns3404:listitem>
  <ns3406:listitem xmlns:ns3406="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><ns3407:para xmlns:ns3407="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">More difficult to keep your systems portable across platforms.</ns3407:para></ns3406:listitem>
</ns3401:itemizedlist>
</ns3400:para>
    
</ns3397:section>